body:
I get the same error like @levifussell when I try to run the code given in the official PyTorch tutorial [here](http://pytorch.org/tutorials/intermediate/reinforcement_q_learning.html). It only occurs at the line `env.render()`. If `env.render()` is called above `import torch` the error occurs at `import torch`. I'm running it directly from the terminal on Ubuntu 14.04.

EDIT: I just went back to PyTorch v0.12 and it works. Earlier I was running v0.2
